\begin_layout Standard
The nonlinear optical response of excitons in 2D materials can be simulated
 using real-time equation of motion techniques.
 Here we perform simulations using hexagonal boron nitride (hBN), see Methods
 section.
 The choice of this specific material was based on two reasons: it is a
 prototypical 2d semiconductor 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Roldn2017"
literal "false"

\end_inset

