 amplitude of low-order harmonics decays as the order is increased, until
 the energy of the harmonics equals the band gap of the material, roughly
 at the tenth harmonic.
 At this point, a plateau of high-harmonics emerges, but once they reach
 their cutoff condition (around the 30th harmonic), an exponential decay
